Operatives of the Department of State Services have barricaded all roads leading to the premises of the Federal High Court in Abuja, as the trial of the leader of the Indigenous People of Biafra, Nnamdi Kanu, resumed today. Also, journalists were barred from the court premises. It was learnt that Kanu arrived at the court around 11 am. The IPOB leader is facing 15 charges bordering on terrorism and felony before Justice Binta Nyako of the Federal High Court in Abuja. Details laterâ€¦